WEBVTT

00:13.430 --> 00:16.182
Of course, Mr. Zero. Understood.

00:18.351 --> 00:20.228
I apologize for keeping you waiting.

00:20.729 --> 00:24.315
We are tying up
some especially pesky loose ends.

00:24.816 --> 00:27.776
I believe you have a history
with one of them.

00:27.777 --> 00:30.071
Princess Vivi of Alabasta?

00:32.949 --> 00:35.576
Cobra's blue-haired brat.

00:35.577 --> 00:36.994
I heard she went missing.

00:36.995 --> 00:39.247
And Mr. Zero would like to ensure
she's never found.

00:39.873 --> 00:42.083
Now, how can I help you?

00:42.584 --> 00:45.627
Oh, I came to speak to the man in charge.

00:45.628 --> 00:47.547
Not some secretary.

00:48.214 --> 00:50.300
Delicious as she might be.

00:51.342 --> 00:54.094
Unfortunately, Mr. Zero
is otherwise occupied.

00:54.095 --> 00:55.471
This is an insult.

00:55.472 --> 00:56.805
You disrespect my king.

00:56.806 --> 00:59.433
A king currently
in exile from his own kingdom,

00:59.434 --> 01:02.102
who requires the aid of my organization
to get it back.

01:02.103 --> 01:05.690
Unless you'd prefer to keep sailing
around the Grand Line playing pirate?

01:13.823 --> 01:16.033
I have been very generous

01:16.034 --> 01:20.329
with my financial contributions
to Baroque Works.

01:20.330 --> 01:24.501
But you tell your leader
there's no such thing as a free lunch.

01:25.126 --> 01:26.544
I want

01:27.170 --> 01:29.129
what I'm owed!

01:29.130 --> 01:31.006
Sire, your blood pressure.

01:31.007 --> 01:32.758
Funny you mentioned lunch.

01:32.759 --> 01:37.513
The symbol of Drum Kingdom's royal family
is a woolly hippo, is it not?

01:37.514 --> 01:40.015
An animal known
for its voracious appetite.

01:40.016 --> 01:41.558
Mmm.

01:41.559 --> 01:43.311
Well, rest assured,

01:43.853 --> 01:46.106
we have no intention
of leaving you hungry.

01:47.315 --> 01:49.149
Blackbeard has vacated Drum.

01:49.150 --> 01:50.192
Mm-hmm.

01:50.193 --> 01:53.404
Mr. Zero thinks
it's time you reclaim your birthright.

01:54.030 --> 01:55.824
He feels a king

01:57.033 --> 01:59.369
would make a valuable ally.

02:02.163 --> 02:03.331
Hmm.

02:11.631 --> 02:12.674
Is this…

02:13.299 --> 02:15.342
A gift.

02:15.343 --> 02:19.514
A token of gratitude
for your financial contributions.

02:25.937 --> 02:27.939
What do you get for the king

02:28.773 --> 02:30.358
who has everything?

02:33.319 --> 02:35.196
A devil fruit!

02:37.198 --> 02:39.032
What power does this one hold?

02:39.033 --> 02:40.743
Well, that's the fun, isn't it?

02:43.663 --> 02:45.123
Take a bite and find out.

02:57.510 --> 02:58.595
Mmm!

02:59.721 --> 03:00.722
Bon appétit.

03:29.209 --> 03:30.251
Sanji?

03:30.835 --> 03:31.669
What…

03:32.170 --> 03:33.253
How…

03:33.254 --> 03:35.965
You're okay. You're okay.
Do you want some food?

03:36.716 --> 03:40.636
I made you, uh, some fresh consommé.
I ran out of chicken stock,

03:40.637 --> 03:43.513
but it turns out that dinosaur
is a very versatile ingredient.

03:43.514 --> 03:45.350
I'm not hungry.

03:46.768 --> 03:47.685
Well…

03:50.063 --> 03:51.606
you need to eat something.

03:53.524 --> 03:55.651
- I've been trying, but--
- Sanji, I'm fine.

03:55.652 --> 04:00.531
I just passed out at dinner last night.
I must've been more tired than I thought.

04:04.410 --> 04:05.912
Nami, that was four days ago.

04:10.250 --> 04:11.084
What?

04:12.252 --> 04:14.128
You've been in and out since you fainted.

04:15.088 --> 04:17.298
I've been here the whole time.

04:17.924 --> 04:18.841
Uh…

04:19.509 --> 04:21.886
It's probably just heatstroke. I…

04:26.516 --> 04:27.891
No.

04:27.892 --> 04:29.894
I think that…

04:31.896 --> 04:33.690
I think that something happened

04:34.190 --> 04:35.316
at Little Garden.

04:36.317 --> 04:37.902
I don't know what, but…

04:38.486 --> 04:39.362
but it's okay

04:40.613 --> 04:42.115
because we're getting you help.

04:46.369 --> 04:47.370
Okay.

05:02.552 --> 05:03.636
Thank you…

05:05.888 --> 05:07.515
for worrying about me.

05:08.308 --> 05:09.851
I always worry about you.

05:58.316 --> 05:59.525
Aren't you cold?

06:01.069 --> 06:02.236
Could be warmer,

06:03.529 --> 06:04.447
I guess.

06:05.448 --> 06:07.367
You know,
everybody else has got a shirt on.

06:10.161 --> 06:11.829
If you insist.

06:18.044 --> 06:19.462
How's Nami doing?

06:19.962 --> 06:22.465
She's asleep again,
but it's getting worse.

06:23.299 --> 06:24.675
Her fever's still sky-high.

06:26.135 --> 06:28.846
- We need to find a doctor.
- We don't even know where we are.

06:29.347 --> 06:30.931
How are we gonna find a doctor?

06:30.932 --> 06:33.100
What about Alabasta?
You have doctors there, don't you?

06:33.101 --> 06:35.477
We could be days,
maybe weeks from Alabasta.

06:35.478 --> 06:37.438
Nami doesn't have that kind of time.

06:38.231 --> 06:39.565
We have to try.

06:40.191 --> 06:42.527
You wanna get home
as soon as possible, don't you?

06:44.654 --> 06:47.115
I do need to get home as soon as possible.

06:52.370 --> 06:54.621
Which is why we're gonna stop
at the first island we find

06:54.622 --> 06:55.832
and get Nami help.

06:56.707 --> 06:58.418
Then we make to Alabasta.

06:59.293 --> 07:02.046
That's well said. Thank you, Vivi.

07:03.881 --> 07:04.715
Exactly.

07:05.425 --> 07:06.884
That is the fastest way.

07:12.974 --> 07:14.392
Sounds like a plan.

07:42.628 --> 07:45.213
So this is the communications outpost?

07:45.214 --> 07:49.176
Better to be discreet when the job
is intercepting and tracing calls.

07:49.177 --> 07:50.344
Hope they have a shower.

07:52.513 --> 07:53.514
What?

07:54.849 --> 07:56.476
We could both use one.

08:00.771 --> 08:03.065
All right, let's make this fast.

08:03.941 --> 08:05.942
Get a comm snail and radio Marine fort.

08:05.943 --> 08:07.819
Tell them we've been
up and down the Grand Line

08:07.820 --> 08:09.197
and found no sign of Baroque Works.

08:09.780 --> 08:12.240
Can't capture an agent alive
if we can't find one.

08:12.241 --> 08:14.618
How do you think
Vice Admiral Garp's gonna take it?

08:14.619 --> 08:17.205
Ah, we've indulged this wild goose chase
long enough.

08:17.830 --> 08:21.000
- It's time to go after the Straw Hats.
- They could be anywhere by now.

08:22.335 --> 08:24.629
This again? Do we need to get you a cane?

08:25.922 --> 08:26.923
Captain?

08:30.384 --> 08:31.843
Sword wounds.

08:31.844 --> 08:32.887
Pirates.

08:33.387 --> 08:34.638
Not just any pirates.

08:34.639 --> 08:36.807
These wounds were made
by a skilled swordsman.

08:39.560 --> 08:40.811
Straw Hats.

08:48.819 --> 08:52.365
Why would the Straw Hats go out
of their way to attack a comms outpost?

08:58.287 --> 09:01.248
Find the commander's office. Call it in.

09:01.249 --> 09:02.667
What if you need backup?

09:03.501 --> 09:04.335
I won't.

09:29.527 --> 09:31.487
Luffy, we found an island!

09:48.045 --> 09:49.589
Look at all the snow.

09:53.467 --> 09:54.677
It's so white!

09:55.595 --> 09:56.637
Drum Kingdom.

09:57.388 --> 09:58.598
You recognize this place?

10:00.224 --> 10:02.684
Lucky for us, it's a nation
renowned throughout the Grand Line

10:02.685 --> 10:03.894
for its medical expertise.

10:04.687 --> 10:07.481
Oh, that's great. There'll be
tons of doctors there, then, no?

10:08.065 --> 10:09.567
Or snow monsters.

10:11.068 --> 10:13.194
That possibility should be factored in!

10:13.195 --> 10:17.491
When we arrive, it might be best
if we keep my identity a secret.

10:18.075 --> 10:19.702
'Cause you're an assassin or a princess?

10:21.412 --> 10:25.583
From what I've been told,
the people of Drum are welcoming and kind.

10:26.792 --> 10:28.002
But there is some history.

10:29.128 --> 10:32.340
The politics between Drum and Alabasta
are… tenuous.

10:34.759 --> 10:36.051
What does that mean?

10:36.052 --> 10:38.928
It means someone on the island
hates Vivi's guts.

10:38.929 --> 10:40.014
Do you wanna tell us who?

10:41.932 --> 10:43.017
Their king.

10:44.143 --> 10:45.269
Wapol.

10:46.312 --> 10:49.023
Royal conflict isn't the kind of problem
we need right now.

10:50.983 --> 10:52.526
We have no other choice.

10:53.444 --> 10:55.363
This is our only option to save Nami.

11:02.036 --> 11:04.038
Then let's go find us a doctor.

11:16.008 --> 11:18.928
The reverie will now come to order.

11:19.845 --> 11:22.139
Welcome, fellow nobles.

11:23.391 --> 11:25.226
I, Thalassa Lucas,

11:26.227 --> 11:29.104
King of Ilisia,
call this reverie to order.

11:29.105 --> 11:35.736
Before we begin, I would like to once
again extend our thanks to the Marines

11:36.320 --> 11:40.532
for their protection during our travels
and these proceedings.

11:40.533 --> 11:45.286
And where are the warlords of the sea?
Hmm?

11:45.287 --> 11:49.874
Remind me again
why we give those criminals free rein

11:49.875 --> 11:52.211
if they aren't around to protect us,

11:52.712 --> 11:54.380
let alone our kingdoms.

11:54.964 --> 11:58.884
Warlords exist as a deterrent
for other pirates.

11:59.385 --> 12:02.847
An important check
to the power balance of the seas.

12:03.347 --> 12:05.724
And how did that work out for the fishmen?

12:05.725 --> 12:09.269
Their queen was assassinated a while back,

12:09.270 --> 12:13.565
and not even the fishmen warlord
could stop it.

12:13.566 --> 12:18.528
If those among us wish to question
the efficacy of the warlords,

12:18.529 --> 12:22.783
perhaps they should run for chairman
and put it on the docket.

12:25.369 --> 12:28.622
Today, we have
a more pressing threat to address.

12:33.878 --> 12:36.922
He is known only as Dragon.

12:37.923 --> 12:40.633
Though his numbers are modest now,

12:40.634 --> 12:44.847
his revolutionary army
grows more every day.

12:45.347 --> 12:49.477
I believe there is no greater threat
to the World Government,

12:50.227 --> 12:53.397
to our prosperity, to our stability,

12:53.898 --> 12:55.191
than this man.

12:56.317 --> 12:59.487
We must not ignore the danger…

13:01.197 --> 13:02.948
…the danger that he…

13:03.491 --> 13:05.951
Something else to add, King Wapol?

13:07.495 --> 13:09.788
Me?

13:09.789 --> 13:10.623
Always.

13:17.171 --> 13:18.631
That's fine.

13:19.924 --> 13:21.925
Rebellion schmabellion.

13:21.926 --> 13:25.763
The people of Drum Kingdom are happy.

13:26.430 --> 13:29.058
I provide them with food and water,

13:29.809 --> 13:32.185
an army for their protection,

13:32.186 --> 13:36.731
and the best medical care in the world.

13:36.732 --> 13:42.529
And should any of my subjects
become ungrateful for my generosity,

13:42.530 --> 13:47.660
then I can always take my gifts away.

13:54.166 --> 13:55.709
May I have the floor?

13:56.710 --> 14:00.631
The chair recognizes
King Cobra of Alabasta.

14:02.758 --> 14:06.762
Revolutions are also
an expression of human emotion.

14:08.097 --> 14:10.723
People whose voices are not heard

14:10.724 --> 14:12.434
cannot truly be happy.

14:13.185 --> 14:16.605
There was a time when one could hear
the people's laughter in your kingdom.

14:17.982 --> 14:19.941
Well, someone's into old tales.

14:19.942 --> 14:22.528
Drum once had a king
who listened to his people.

14:23.279 --> 14:26.031
Well, I couldn't stand my father.

14:26.782 --> 14:31.120
He hadn't the slightest clue
what it meant to rule.

14:31.620 --> 14:35.206
And now I am king.

14:35.207 --> 14:38.877
A king is but a man,
and a crown is just a hat.

14:38.878 --> 14:42.505
It is the kingdom that endures.

14:42.506 --> 14:44.842
I am the kingdom!

14:47.803 --> 14:51.973
Politics is about power,

14:51.974 --> 14:53.725
not feelings.

14:53.726 --> 14:58.313
And I'd sooner hear wisdom
from one of your sandpit's giant ducks

14:58.314 --> 15:00.231
than listen to another second

15:00.232 --> 15:04.986
of your prattling on
about the laughter in the hills.

15:04.987 --> 15:07.030
- Enough!
- Do you know what I do…

15:07.031 --> 15:08.781
Enough!

15:08.782 --> 15:12.202
- I'll tell you when it's enough!
- Order!

15:57.748 --> 16:00.334
Here comes the heat.

16:02.795 --> 16:05.713
Way to keep your eye on the ball, slugger.

16:05.714 --> 16:07.090
What the hell are you?

16:07.091 --> 16:09.342
Stepping up to the mound,

16:09.343 --> 16:10.886
it's Miss Thursday.

16:14.431 --> 16:17.183
- Baroque Works.
- You've heard of us.

16:17.184 --> 16:19.144
Talk about an unforced error.

16:39.081 --> 16:41.708
Guess not everyone's ready for the majors.

16:41.709 --> 16:43.419
Enough baseball jokes.

17:11.739 --> 17:12.656
Hit the bench.

17:14.575 --> 17:17.244
Now she's got me doing it.

17:17.828 --> 17:19.997
So much for taking one alive.

18:03.332 --> 18:04.332
Where are we?

18:04.333 --> 18:06.627
We're getting you help. Just stay with us.

18:10.130 --> 18:11.340
What the hell was that?

18:12.007 --> 18:14.218
The last warning shot
they'll ever get off.

18:14.927 --> 18:17.011
Stop right there, pirates!

18:17.012 --> 18:19.931
Turn back at once,
or face the consequences.

18:19.932 --> 18:21.307
We saw your ship.

18:21.308 --> 18:25.228
- You can't fool us.
- We have a sick crewmate who needs help!

18:25.229 --> 18:28.272
Leave this country alone,
you lying pirates!

18:28.273 --> 18:30.317
We need a doctor!

18:31.860 --> 18:32.945
Vivi!

18:35.572 --> 18:37.241
You assholes!

18:37.866 --> 18:41.160
Stop! All of you!

18:41.161 --> 18:43.162
Your impulsiveness
will not solve anything.

18:43.163 --> 18:45.289
If you get us killed,
what will happen to Nami?

18:45.290 --> 18:47.251
You are the captain. Think!

18:53.632 --> 18:55.217
We are very sorry.

18:56.135 --> 18:58.303
If we cannot enter your village,

18:59.221 --> 19:01.515
please spare us a doctor out here.

19:02.432 --> 19:04.726
Our friend is gravely ill.

19:05.227 --> 19:06.562
Please help us.

19:23.996 --> 19:25.330
I'm sorry.

19:26.498 --> 19:27.833
I was wrong!

19:34.214 --> 19:35.257
Please!

19:36.550 --> 19:37.759
Help our friend.

19:51.481 --> 19:53.025
That was very smart, Vivi.

20:03.327 --> 20:04.453
Are you all right?

20:07.539 --> 20:08.624
I'll be fine.

20:13.295 --> 20:15.923
All of you, come with me.

20:50.666 --> 20:52.501
Wow, here comes the welcoming committee.

20:53.210 --> 20:54.669
Is she gonna shoot us again?

20:54.670 --> 20:56.255
Please forgive Maria.

20:56.880 --> 20:58.215
We've all been

20:59.424 --> 21:00.841
on edge.

21:00.842 --> 21:02.261
Sorry, Dalton.

21:03.971 --> 21:05.222
Sorry, pirates.

21:06.890 --> 21:08.850
The villagers here aren't soldiers.

21:09.643 --> 21:11.228
They're civilians.

21:11.895 --> 21:14.356
Prone to itchy trigger fingers.

21:20.070 --> 21:21.822
But after what they've been through,

21:23.198 --> 21:24.533
it's understandable.

21:26.118 --> 21:27.202
Are you the king?

21:28.328 --> 21:29.788
My name is Dalton,

21:30.330 --> 21:32.206
captain of the Civilian Guard.

21:32.207 --> 21:33.667
I don't understand.

21:34.167 --> 21:36.628
What happened here? Where's King Wapol?

21:37.212 --> 21:40.882
A pirate named Blackbeard
laid siege to our village.

21:42.175 --> 21:45.345
He was a man
fueled by bloodshed and carnage.

21:46.221 --> 21:48.682
When his Jolly Roger
showed up on the horizon,

21:49.349 --> 21:51.393
the country was left defenseless.

21:52.144 --> 21:53.770
We couldn't hold Blackbeard off.

21:54.771 --> 21:57.648
Only endured
until he'd had his fill and left.

21:57.649 --> 22:01.528
You're saying Wapol's forces
had no chance against Blackbeard's crew?

22:03.030 --> 22:05.866
I'm saying the king and his soldiers
didn't even try.

22:07.367 --> 22:09.828
Once Wapol saw Blackbeard's power…

22:12.080 --> 22:13.540
he abandoned us all.

22:14.249 --> 22:16.584
And he has the nerve
to call himself a king.

22:16.585 --> 22:20.254
- Vivi.
- How could he do that to his people?

22:20.255 --> 22:22.924
What about the doctors?
Hopefully one of them survived.

22:23.967 --> 22:25.718
Wapol took all the doctors with him.

22:25.719 --> 22:27.762
Great. So we've
wasted our time for nothing.

22:27.763 --> 22:28.805
Except one.

22:30.766 --> 22:31.849
Her name is Kureha.

22:31.850 --> 22:33.018
The witch.

22:34.478 --> 22:36.062
Did you just say witch?

22:36.063 --> 22:38.815
She's taken over Drum Castle
at the top of the mountain.

22:42.194 --> 22:44.111
She's the only one
who can help your friend.

22:44.112 --> 22:47.115
Her medicine is dangerous. Unnatural.

22:47.783 --> 22:52.620
I've seen her flying through the sky under
a full moon with the beast of the forest.

22:52.621 --> 22:54.206
And there's a beast?

22:54.998 --> 22:56.415
Mm-mm. Mm-mm.

22:56.416 --> 22:59.503
- I knew it.
- I'm not scared of a witch.

23:00.170 --> 23:01.546
Or a beast.

23:02.381 --> 23:04.216
If she can save Nami,

23:05.634 --> 23:07.386
then we have to get up there.

23:09.012 --> 23:10.097
How do we get up there?

23:11.681 --> 23:13.141
There was a gondola.

23:14.267 --> 23:17.813
But Wapol destroyed it, trying
to protect his palace from Blackbeard.

23:19.064 --> 23:22.526
You'll have to take the path
on the far side of the mountain. But…

23:24.528 --> 23:26.780
you'll never make the trek by nightfall.

23:29.991 --> 23:32.327
You can stay in the tavern until morning.

23:33.703 --> 23:35.455
I'm sorry we don't have more to offer.

23:37.582 --> 23:39.584
I hope your friend will make it
through the night.

23:40.961 --> 23:42.629
I must get back to my watch.

24:34.556 --> 24:35.432
Ha.

24:40.979 --> 24:43.856
Ah. Not bad.

24:43.857 --> 24:46.234
Not great, but not bad.

24:49.654 --> 24:50.696
You have Kashu.

24:50.697 --> 24:53.700
I haven't heard that. I prefer "style."

24:54.201 --> 24:55.368
Your sword, you idiot.

24:56.036 --> 24:59.580
Kashu.
It's one of the 50 Skillful Grade Swords.

24:59.581 --> 25:03.043
You know, I never thought
to give it a name.

25:03.793 --> 25:05.921
How about Walter?

25:06.505 --> 25:08.464
It doesn't belong
in the hands of an assassin.

25:08.465 --> 25:09.633
Oh.

25:10.133 --> 25:14.304
Well, by all means, dear girl,
come and take it.

25:40.497 --> 25:42.248
I think when I beat you,

25:42.249 --> 25:44.084
I'll take <i>your</i> sword.

25:55.053 --> 25:56.930
You will never touch that sword again.

26:01.643 --> 26:02.561
Huh.

26:09.526 --> 26:10.527
So…

26:12.654 --> 26:14.655
…how did Baroque Works know
we were coming?

26:14.656 --> 26:15.782
They didn't.

26:18.076 --> 26:20.161
Communications room was trashed.

26:20.996 --> 26:23.373
- They were looking for something.
- Like what?

26:24.958 --> 26:26.167
Let's find out.

26:58.992 --> 27:01.620
Luffy, we can't wait till morning.

27:02.996 --> 27:04.456
What do you want to do, Luffy?

27:08.960 --> 27:11.463
If we can't go around the mountain…

27:14.090 --> 27:15.800
then we go straight up.

27:20.305 --> 27:22.015
You want to climb it?

27:24.184 --> 27:27.103
Nami can't make that.
None of us can make that.

27:31.149 --> 27:32.233
Nami.

27:37.030 --> 27:39.866
The only doctor here
lives on top of a mountain.

27:40.784 --> 27:42.744
We're gonna have to climb it
to get to her.

27:43.244 --> 27:44.871
I'll carry you on my back.

27:45.538 --> 27:46.623
Are you okay with that?

27:48.750 --> 27:51.628
It's going to be night soon.
It's impossible.

27:52.128 --> 27:53.129
Death.

27:53.713 --> 27:55.674
Certain and inevitable death.

28:04.224 --> 28:05.934
I'm counting on you, Captain.

28:09.104 --> 28:10.480
Leave everything to me.

28:11.648 --> 28:12.941
Fine. I'm coming too.

28:13.817 --> 28:14.942
Me too.

28:14.943 --> 28:17.653
No, you've got to stay.
Vivi can't make the climb with her arm.

28:17.654 --> 28:21.073
And Baroque Works is still out there
looking for us, so someone's gotta stay.

28:21.074 --> 28:22.450
I'll stay too.

28:23.868 --> 28:28.707
And get Zoro's back, just in case
the witch feeds you to the beast.

28:30.542 --> 28:31.543
All right.

28:33.336 --> 28:35.422
We'll come back after we save Nami.

28:51.104 --> 28:52.105
Should hold.

28:58.486 --> 29:00.488
My jacket should keep you extra warm.

29:25.638 --> 29:26.723
Here we go.

30:17.482 --> 30:19.609
What if this witch can't heal Nami?

30:21.402 --> 30:22.654
We just have to believe.

30:23.822 --> 30:26.032
I should have gone instead of the cook,
shouldn't I?

30:26.616 --> 30:27.825
Sanji will be fine.

30:27.826 --> 30:30.327
Are you even listening?
We should go up there now--

30:30.328 --> 30:32.330
Zoro, do something else.

30:33.748 --> 30:35.124
Like I'm doing something.

30:35.875 --> 30:38.460
Stop asking questions
and hovering over me,

30:38.461 --> 30:40.797
and do something
because this is not helping.

30:51.349 --> 30:52.767
You could've asked nicely.

30:57.105 --> 30:58.857
I'm gonna join Dalton on watch.

31:00.900 --> 31:01.860
Good.

31:05.738 --> 31:06.989
<i>Now, Princess Vivi,</i>

31:06.990 --> 31:09.658
you were supposed to be
on your father's ship.

31:09.659 --> 31:11.994
As far as he knows, I am.

31:11.995 --> 31:13.203
Princess…

31:13.204 --> 31:16.040
Igaram, I couldn't just stay
in my quarters. It's a reverie.

31:16.708 --> 31:19.335
I wanted to see it with my own eyes.
Or at least hear it.

31:19.836 --> 31:22.045
My father just gave
that King Wapol an earful--

31:22.046 --> 31:25.757
Princess Vivi, you are next in line
for the throne of Alabasta.

31:25.758 --> 31:29.387
But until that time, you are not permitted
to hear what happens inside that room.

31:29.888 --> 31:30.888
No one is.

31:30.889 --> 31:34.267
How am I supposed to learn how to lead
a kingdom if I'm stuck on a ship?

31:35.184 --> 31:36.227
Hmm.

31:38.229 --> 31:41.566
Perhaps I could arrange
for a tour of the grounds.

31:42.233 --> 31:45.612
See how the World Government operations
work, and

31:47.030 --> 31:48.697
I won't tell your father you snuck out.

31:48.698 --> 31:49.948
As my royal guardian,

31:49.949 --> 31:52.452
that seems like that would get <i>you</i>
in more trouble than me.

31:53.661 --> 31:55.955
- You--
- Throw in ice cream and we have a deal.

32:00.543 --> 32:02.086
Your first treaty.

32:03.713 --> 32:04.672
I'm proud.

32:06.925 --> 32:07.926
Now, stay here.

32:10.345 --> 32:12.471
The audacity!

32:12.472 --> 32:14.891
Does that fool
not know who he's dealing with?

32:16.476 --> 32:18.895
A grave disrespect for sure, Your Majesty.

32:23.691 --> 32:25.943
Out of my way, child!

32:25.944 --> 32:27.236
Your Highness!

32:28.029 --> 32:29.572
Oh my goodness!

32:30.323 --> 32:32.951
You would dare strike
the Princess of Alabasta?

32:34.285 --> 32:38.289
Oh no! Oh, the Princess of Alabasta!

32:39.165 --> 32:45.004
How unfortunate you are to be
the daughter of that worthless fool!

32:47.423 --> 32:48.841
It's all right.

32:50.385 --> 32:51.719
Sorry I bumped into you.

32:59.185 --> 33:01.521
Let's go!

33:04.399 --> 33:06.650
Get out of my way!

33:06.651 --> 33:07.694
I'm sorry.

33:33.344 --> 33:34.594
Your Highness,

33:34.595 --> 33:36.889
you were magnificent today.

33:37.807 --> 33:41.019
Never have I witnessed
such an act of bravery.

33:42.687 --> 33:46.941
Princess Vivi, you averted
a great potential conflict.

33:54.782 --> 33:55.950
Listen to me.

33:57.076 --> 33:58.703
Watching you today,

33:59.579 --> 34:03.916
I already know how you will lead Alabasta
when the time comes.

34:08.171 --> 34:09.088
Come.

34:22.769 --> 34:24.270
<i>You're awful quiet over there.</i>

34:27.565 --> 34:29.901
I thought you weren't interested
in hearing worries.

34:32.945 --> 34:34.697
Look, I'm nervous too.

34:35.782 --> 34:38.493
But those guys will stop at nothing
to get Nami the help she needs.

34:41.954 --> 34:43.664
It's not just about Nami.

34:45.917 --> 34:49.795
This kingdom used to be prosperous.

34:49.796 --> 34:52.589
They were on the cutting edge of medicine,

34:52.590 --> 34:55.927
and now they have nothing.

34:56.969 --> 34:59.555
All because of their king.

35:02.558 --> 35:03.642
Vivi…

35:03.643 --> 35:09.023
And… and Alabasta… I have been
away from home for so long.

35:10.983 --> 35:14.111
How do I know
that things haven't gotten worse?

35:14.112 --> 35:19.658
How do I know that what's happened here
hasn't happened to my home as well?

35:19.659 --> 35:22.078
Vivi. You can't…

35:24.664 --> 35:27.416
carry the weight of the world
on your shoulders alone.

35:30.294 --> 35:32.505
You can't solve every problem by yourself.

35:34.507 --> 35:35.466
I just…

35:38.678 --> 35:41.597
I just want to do something.

35:49.814 --> 35:51.023
I get it.

35:54.735 --> 35:57.196
You could start
by handing me that wrench over there.

36:06.455 --> 36:07.582
Look at that.

36:34.066 --> 36:35.818
Doctor.

36:36.777 --> 36:38.571
Doctor.

36:40.031 --> 36:41.699
Doctor.

36:53.336 --> 36:54.712
Luffy!

36:55.213 --> 36:56.714
We're almost there!

36:59.967 --> 37:01.177
Luffy…

37:06.307 --> 37:07.683
Hold on, Nami.

37:34.043 --> 37:34.961
Luffy!

37:40.466 --> 37:42.801
Luffy!

37:42.802 --> 37:44.303
Are you okay?

37:56.774 --> 38:00.319
- No!
- Just get her to the top!

38:58.669 --> 39:00.588
What a pretty castle.

39:26.030 --> 39:27.114
Hey.

39:31.494 --> 39:32.787
Save

39:33.371 --> 39:34.330
my

39:36.040 --> 39:37.208
friends.

39:50.054 --> 39:51.972
Why is Baroque Works here?

39:52.848 --> 39:54.392
Haven't you heard?

39:55.518 --> 39:57.520
Our motto is mystery.

39:58.437 --> 39:59.688
I have a motto too.

40:02.483 --> 40:04.693
Tell me what I wanna know,

40:05.277 --> 40:08.489
or I'll shove a baseball down your throat,
like I did your partner.

40:13.411 --> 40:14.912
Go ahead.

40:15.413 --> 40:17.289
I completed my mission.

40:17.957 --> 40:19.834
My work here is done.

40:32.805 --> 40:36.433
Sir, we need him alive.
We didn't get any information out of him.

40:36.434 --> 40:37.309
Calm down.

40:38.185 --> 40:39.812
He's just taking a nap.

40:41.272 --> 40:42.314
Besides,

40:43.190 --> 40:44.900
I think I know what they were after.

40:46.444 --> 40:47.778
He won't talk.

40:48.737 --> 40:50.156
But maybe this one will.

40:51.949 --> 40:54.076
If we can keep it alive long enough.

41:06.297 --> 41:07.631
How is your friend?

41:09.258 --> 41:11.844
Some of them took her
up the mountain to find the witch.

41:14.722 --> 41:16.348
They couldn't wait until morning?

41:21.103 --> 41:24.397
I don't know whether to marvel
at their perseverance

41:24.398 --> 41:27.275
or shudder at their foolhardiness.

41:27.276 --> 41:28.444
Yeah.

41:29.653 --> 41:30.988
That's our captain.

41:33.115 --> 41:35.701
Do you really think
this Blackbeard is coming back?

41:37.369 --> 41:39.121
Hopefully, he's had his fill

41:40.289 --> 41:41.707
and will not return.

41:42.500 --> 41:45.503
But he isn't the only abomination
we're up against.

41:49.465 --> 41:52.301
You're looking for your king. Wapol.

41:53.969 --> 41:55.971
He is a cruel man

41:57.264 --> 41:59.099
with an insatiable hunger.

42:01.936 --> 42:04.813
And I know that he will try
to reclaim what once was his.

42:08.234 --> 42:11.070
This… village…

42:13.030 --> 42:15.824
is finally beginning
to recover from his reign.

42:17.409 --> 42:19.411
And I hope we can build something new.

42:22.748 --> 42:24.124
A peaceful nation.

42:24.959 --> 42:27.086
And who's gonna lead this nation?

42:28.003 --> 42:29.004
You?

42:31.173 --> 42:32.591
No, I'm not.

42:35.261 --> 42:37.763
My aim is not to lead these people.

42:40.057 --> 42:42.017
Only to be a shield for them.

42:45.604 --> 42:47.439
You don't always get a choice.

42:57.241 --> 42:59.326
I'm more of a sword guy myself.

43:02.329 --> 43:03.747
I could lend you mine,

43:04.248 --> 43:05.708
should the need arise.

43:52.004 --> 43:53.339
You're all right.

44:07.811 --> 44:08.937
Hello?

44:20.324 --> 44:21.283
Are you

44:22.326 --> 44:23.242
hiding?

44:23.243 --> 44:25.537
Of course! That's why you can't see me.

44:27.039 --> 44:29.166
- You're peeking the wrong way.
- Shut up!

44:33.253 --> 44:35.923
Are you… feeling better?

44:37.174 --> 44:39.093
A little bit, yeah.

44:40.678 --> 44:42.721
Are you the one
that's been taking care of me?

44:51.146 --> 44:52.314
That'd be me.

44:56.902 --> 44:57.778
I'm Kureha.

44:59.113 --> 45:00.864
You can call me Doctorine.

45:01.365 --> 45:06.453
And lucky for you, I am the last
and greatest physician on Drum Island.

45:10.874 --> 45:11.875
Hmm.

45:12.793 --> 45:15.337
100.76.

45:15.838 --> 45:18.339
Fever's gone down a smidge, which means…

45:18.340 --> 45:19.799
The antibodies are working!

45:19.800 --> 45:23.928
Correct. Treatment's not over yet.
Patient still needs?

45:23.929 --> 45:26.264
Further rounds of antibiotics
and more bed rest.

45:26.265 --> 45:27.766
Hmm. Right again.

45:29.393 --> 45:31.144
No, really, I'm feeling much better.

45:31.145 --> 45:34.314
Thank you so much for your help,
but I need to get…

45:34.815 --> 45:38.026
Only two ways
a patient leaves my care, girly.

45:38.777 --> 45:43.073
Fully recovered or dead.
You're not going anywhere.

45:46.702 --> 45:50.788
You need to rest. Doctorine says
you were bitten by a Kestia.

45:50.789 --> 45:51.832
That's right.

45:52.332 --> 45:53.751
Nasty little buggers.

45:54.251 --> 45:58.296
An infectious tick whose bite
infects the victim with virulent bacteria.

45:58.297 --> 46:02.467
Fever never goes below 104,
which eventually ravages the victim.

46:02.468 --> 46:04.510
We are talking super infection.

46:04.511 --> 46:08.139
Myocarditis. Arteritis. Encephalitis.

46:08.140 --> 46:09.516
I get it. It's bad.

46:11.935 --> 46:15.021
Kind of impressed
you managed to get bit by such a thing.

46:15.022 --> 46:17.982
- Kestia are supposed to be long extinct.
- Mm-hmm.

46:17.983 --> 46:21.569
So unless you were traipsing
through some steamy prehistoric jungle

46:21.570 --> 46:22.987
with your skin exposed--

46:22.988 --> 46:24.198
I was.

46:26.033 --> 46:27.075
You're a strange one.

46:29.953 --> 46:31.330
What about my friends?

46:31.830 --> 46:34.082
A couple of cracked ribs on that one.

46:35.042 --> 46:36.043
And…

46:37.044 --> 46:37.878
and Luffy?

46:43.634 --> 46:44.885
Guys! Guys!

46:45.427 --> 46:47.513
A huge beast dragged us into this castle!

46:48.931 --> 46:51.849
Then this old witch tried to cook me
in a soup and eat me!

46:51.850 --> 46:54.101
Luffy, why are you yelling?

46:54.102 --> 46:56.813
Sanji, we're about to be eaten!

46:56.814 --> 46:59.525
We are not about to be eaten,
and she's not a witch.

47:01.026 --> 47:01.860
I think.

47:03.821 --> 47:06.531
- Nami?
- Nami, you're okay!

47:06.532 --> 47:08.283
Nami, you're fine.

47:08.909 --> 47:10.243
Are you better now?

47:10.244 --> 47:12.119
You're all better now.

47:12.120 --> 47:13.663
I gave her antibiotics.

47:13.664 --> 47:15.164
I reset his ribs.

47:15.165 --> 47:18.085
I put you in warm water
to prevent hypothermia.

47:21.088 --> 47:21.964
Oh.

47:22.506 --> 47:23.632
Okay.

47:24.591 --> 47:25.759
Thanks, Grandma.

47:26.718 --> 47:28.011
I'll bill you later.

47:28.512 --> 47:31.430
And like she said, I'm not a witch.

47:31.431 --> 47:33.517
I'm not old either.

47:34.101 --> 47:38.146
I'll have you know,
I am not a day over 139.

47:38.772 --> 47:40.065
Seriously?

47:40.691 --> 47:41.525
Wow.

47:42.025 --> 47:43.318
You're really old.

47:45.904 --> 47:48.197
Okay, but, Nami, can I get you anything?

47:48.198 --> 47:51.784
Actually, I could eat.
I feel like I haven't eaten in days.

47:51.785 --> 47:53.244
- Because you haven't.
- Me too!

47:53.245 --> 47:54.162
You have.

47:54.746 --> 47:56.873
I'm a doctor, not a chef.

47:56.874 --> 47:59.251
Lucky for you, I am.

47:59.918 --> 48:02.420
Chopper, show him where the kitchen is.

48:02.421 --> 48:03.714
Yes, Doctorine.

48:14.016 --> 48:16.018
What are you?

48:26.028 --> 48:27.654
What is that?!
